Key Match Events: The Thunder outscored the Celtics 50-27 in the second half.
Jayson Tatum had 26 points and 10 rebounds for the Celtics while Jaylen Brown added another 21 points.
MVP candidate Shai Gilgeous-Alexander finished with 33 points and 11 rebounds for the Thunder.
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics will have to pick up themselves after Sunday’s tough loss.
They’re now 2-1 on this tough four-game road trip with the 2023 NBA champs coming up on the road.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics were just 3-for-24 on 3-pointers in the second half as their jumpers abandoned them.
It was the Thunder, looking to make their own mark on the league, who came out with the victory Sunday.
